LA SANTA CLARA broke slowly, raced in the two path between horses entering the turn and weakened. BESSIE BLUE , three deep on the turn, dropped back. RACE.RACE_TEXT: LAUREL PARK RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 68. Claiming Purse 26870. (PLUS UP TO 15% MBF) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, if for $8,000, allowed 4 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BAD TEMPER rated off the rail, edged up between rivals into the turn, angled out and circled five wide with momentum into the lane, closed nicely under steady hand encouragement, forged past BALLYKEEN leaving the sixteenth marker and drew clear. BALLYKEEN bore out at the break, corrected and dropped in some when edging up early, bumped with SAPPHIRE BEAUTY leaving the chute, tracked three wide into the turn, moved outside to engage the leader mid turn, kicked clear into the lane, kept on under a drive past mid stretch then gave way grudgingly. PERFORMANCEANXIETY settled four to five wide outside rivals early, shifted wider on the turn, circled seven wide into the stretch, straightened and found her best too late. RATIONALMILLENNIAL , bumped and pinched back at the break, was taken to rate early on, moved up off the rail past the five sixteenths, steadied briefly soon after, shifted in a path to work between runners then closed steadily in the final furlong. VICTORIAN RIVIERA sped clear early, set the pace towards the inside, took pressure mid turn, came two wide for the drive and weakened in the final eighth. IRISH LACE drifted out a bit at the break, corrected and settled while saving ground, stayed along the rail through the drive, made a slight run near the sixteenth pole then flattened out. FASHIONATTA , bumped at the break, moved up and chased two to three wide, made some progress into the lane but failed to sustain. HAPPY TAPPY TIM was hustled up to contention, stalked while saving ground, angled three wide under asking nearing the stretch, chased and gave way. POET IN MY HEART broke inward and bumped with a rival, showed speed then rated back off rivals, raced between rivals leaving the far turn and faded. HEARDITALL , three deep heading to the turn, angled out and made a mild five wide run mid turn, pursued into the stretch then gave way in the final furlong. LOTTACLASS LILSASS was outrun. SAPPHIRE BEAUTY , bumped at the break and then leaving the chute, prompted the pace two wide, failed to keep pace past the five sixteenths and faltered.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: LUCCI vied outside I GOT A ROCK while under confident handling, raced on near even terms into the lane, responded when put to some asking leaving the three sixteenths, shook clear leaving the furlong grounds, kept on under right handed asks and denied BATTLEBUS through the final yards. BATTLEBUS stalked the dueling leaders while outside a rival, was guided four wide into the lane, moved up to loom in mid stretch, switched over to his left lead with a sixteenth remaining and continued willingly. INDEFATIGABLE saved ground, eased for the drive and closed between foes to gain the show. MONTAUK DADDY had speed then rated back off the leaders and saved ground, came out for the drive, chased and lacked a serious finish. W W SPRINGTIME , three wide, was pushed along past the three eighths, moved up a bit past mid stretch and churned on between runners. BACKWOODS BOOGIE checked soon after the break, angled four wide into the lane but came up empty. I GOT A ROCK , away alertly, disputed the pace to the inside of the winner, kept up the fight to mid stretch then weakened in the final sixteenth. BURGEE broke slowly, saved ground while well back into the turn, shifted out for the drive and failed to menace. FLASHINTHENIGHT hit the gate at the break causing his rider to briefly lose his balance, was bumped soon after, saved ground leaving the far turn, angled out and came up empty. REUX (GB) , racing without front shoes, was rated off the pace while saving ground, angled out mid turn, came five wide for the drive and faded. EYE OF GUNFIGHTER , racing without front shoes, was in a bit tight at the break, dropped off the pace and failed to respond.
